reviews.review: Completely horrible from start to finish

A fitting end to a series that has lasted my entire lifetime. I got to have closure with a lot of old faces and storylines. My only gripe was that so much new material was packed into the movie with very little time to develop it.

Growing up with star wars the series isnt up to par. But raise of Skywalker wasnt bad. Better than last jedi. Only 2 parts I thought were dumb and didnt fit into story line. Over all not a bad movie to close out the saga
The acting was very good. It was a good way to bring back old characters. Rey was a very strong woman. The change in Kylo REN was great. Lots of action too.
Star wars the ries of skywalker absolutely awesome And good end get it 10\10. I saw it on Friday i saw it again the next day
A bit cheesy and over the top at times, but what do you expect from the 9th installment of a franchise that has spanned 5 decades
Disregard the critics who do not know or understand the reciprocal approach of how these trilogies work. Go see it! It’s a great finale thoughtfully executed and well acted.

Despite the speed, logic stretch, and lack of risk it's still a ton of fun. The film specifically shines when Rey, Finn, and Poe are together. Adam Driver‘s performance is savage. The young cast really does help rejuvenate the franchise and i look forward to what lies ahead for all of them (regardless if they will/will not be featured again in a galaxy far, far away).

All in all, it's a Star Wars movie. And i for one am thankful i get to experience them on the silver screen.

PS: Props to Anthony Daniels. He absolutely crushed it.
Best of all Star Wars movies.....awesome!

As a Star Wars fan since as early as I can remember I feel this film brilliantly delivered on the nostalgia & fan service from its predecessors, all the way down to the music score which to me personally was a lovely treat. There were a few unexpected twists and turns along the way, but to conclude; this movie was the perfect send off paying respects to an older generation whilst also inviting the new with welcoming arms. My wife and I thoroughly enjoyed the ride, and we are ready to see which direction Disney takes us to expand on what we've grown to love all these years.
